    "body": "> > will this mark be implemented within the scope of this PR?\r\n> \r\n> ah, ok, this is already implemented in develop, but with incorrect color\r\n\r\nI see. Thank you!\r\nOne more question. I noticed that some marks are incorrect for successful toasts. Could you also fix it in the scope of the current task?\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\nRed mark is shown for the removed message\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/212040410-502bd82d-3718-46c6-a50a-0e64f534b0eb.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\ngreen mark is shown for the removed message and for \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/212040070-6e64e04e-6e1a-43ff-ab99-48ced9c79df2.png)\r\n\r\n**Additional info:**\r\nThe same green mark is not shown after succeeded joining the community\r\n**Steps:**\r\n1. Make USER_A and USER_B as mutual contacts \r\n2. Create a community as USER_A\r\n3. Join the community as USER_B\r\n\r\n**Actual result:**\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/212048556-70a42b29-c1a9-4d22-8f75-cb9ad89fc608.png)\r\n\r\n**Expected result:**\r\nthe icon within toast should be in the form of green checkmark\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52490791/212048669-a6fb5d60-ba72-48aa-bc56-41c0d560860c.png)\r\n",
